1
00:00:00,690 --> 00:00:05,620
******you are considering going into
experimental physics,my door is always open.
如果你们对应用物理有兴趣 随时欢迎

2
00:00:05,650 --> 00:00:08,390
Once again,I'm sorry that the
demonstration didn't quite work out,
再次的抱歉 演示不太成功

3
00:00:08,410 --> 00:00:14,130
but now we know what happens when you accidentally
spill Peach Snapple into a helium neon laser.
但至少我们知道了 氦-氖激光管里
不小心洒了桃味饮料的后果

4
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:18,800
Short answer is...don't.
明智的做法是...别那么做

5
00:00:22,710 --> 00:00:28,040
And now to tell you about the theoretical
physics department is Dr. Sheldon Cooper.
接下来给你们讲理论物理的是
Sheldon Cooper博士

6
00:00:31,290 --> 00:00:33,820
- Dr. Cooper?
- Forget it.
- Cooper博士?
- 我不来

7
00:00:35,580 --> 00:00:37,700
Excuse me.
不好意思

8
00:00:38,140 --> 00:00:39,790
Sheldon,we both agreed to do this.
Sheldon我们可商量好了的

9
00:00:39,810 --> 00:00:40,850
It's a waste of time.
这是浪费时间

10
00:00:40,860 --> 00:00:45,270
I might as well explain the laws of
thermodynamics to a bunch of labradoodles.
我还不如去给
一群拉布拉多犬讲解热力学理论

11
00:00:46,630 --> 00:00:51,200
If you don't do this,I won't
take you to the comic book store.
要是不配合
不带你去漫画书店哟

12
00:00:53,170 --> 00:00:55,520
Hello.
大家好

13
00:00:59,250 --> 00:01:02,850
Nice work with the laser,by the way.
我说 激光实验做的不错嘛

14
00:01:04,330 --> 00:01:06,950
Looking out at your fresh young faces,
看着你们这些年轻的新鲜面孔

15
00:01:06,970 --> 00:01:13,200
I remember when I too was deciding my
academic future as a lowly graduate student.
不禁想起了 当年还是小研究生时
我也如此决定自己的研究方向

16
00:01:13,210 --> 00:01:16,130
Of course,I was 14.
当然 那时我才14岁

17
00:01:16,140 --> 00:01:21,410
And I'd already achieved more than most of
you could ever hope to,despite my 9:00 bedtime.
即使9点就得睡觉 那时也已小有成就
在座大多数至今望尘莫及

18
00:01:22,220 --> 00:01:25,330
Now,there may be one or
two of you in this room
你们中或许有一两位

19
00:01:25,350 --> 00:01:28,980
who has what it takes to
succeed in theoretical physics.
具备天赋 在理论物理上有所建树

20
00:01:29,010 --> 00:01:32,090
Although,it's more likely that you'll spend
your scientific careers teaching fifth graders
当然啦 各位的科学前程
将更有可能教授五年级学生

21
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:35,890
how to make papier mache
volcanoes with baking soda lava.
怎样用烘烤苏打粉
来糊个纸火山

22
00:01:37,150 --> 00:01:39,130
Oh,good God.
仁慈的主呀

23
00:01:39,140 --> 00:01:41,150
In short-- any
one who told you
总之-- 要是有人告诉你们

24
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:44,450
that you would someday be able to make
any significant contribution to physics,
你们有朝一日能对物理做出巨大贡献

25
00:01:44,470 --> 00:01:48,280
played a cruel trick on
you,a cruel trick indeed.
真是忽悠你们
绝对绝对是忽悠惨了

26
00:01:50,290 --> 00:01:53,350
Any questions?
有问题吗?

27
00:01:54,630 --> 00:01:57,890
Of course not.
自然没有了

28
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,780
I weep for the future of science.
真为科学的未来感到悲哀呐

29
00:01:59,790 --> 00:02:03,330
Now if you'll excuse me,the
latest issue of Batman is out.
恕我不奉陪 最新的蝙蝠侠发行了

30
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:06,290
Come,Leonard.
走吧 Leonard

31
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:11,740
Laser demonstration's
looking pretty good now,huh?
现在看来 我的激光演示很棒吧?

32
00:02:12,490 --> 00:02:20,870
荣誉出品

33
00:02:21,890 --> 00:02:30,150
翻译: 王泳东 gigigao 八重樱 饭特稀
校对: 欧屁屁
时间轴: 咔肉肉

34
00:02:30,870 --> 00:02:35,350

35
00:02:36,870 --> 00:02:38,380
I love this time of the year.
每年的这个时节 真叫我倾心

36
00:02:38,390 --> 00:02:41,440
The leaves are turning,there's
a bracing chill in the air.
树叶转色
空中的寒意让人神清气爽

37
00:02:41,450 --> 00:02:46,180
Plus there's a whole new crop of female grad
students about to put on just enough winter weight
再加上新来的一群女研究生
准备在冬天稍微给自己"加点料"

38
00:02:46,190 --> 00:02:48,840
to make them needy and vulnerable.
让自己愈发惹人呵护

39
00:02:50,460 --> 00:02:52,550
That's right,honey,have another calzone.
这就对了嘛 宝贝 再吃块馅饼

40
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:54,600
Daddy can wait.
老爹可以再忍忍

41
00:02:56,550 --> 00:02:59,370
Isn't there a university policy
against dating graduate students?
不是有校规嘛?
不能和研究生约会的

42
00:02:59,380 --> 00:03:01,950
No,if you can talk to
them,you can ask them out.
不是 只要能跟她们搭上话
你可以随便约

43
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:04,840
Damn,there's always a catch.
要死啊! 总给我下套!

44
00:03:04,850 --> 00:03:05,840
Hey,guys.
好呀 小伙子们

45
00:03:05,860 --> 00:03:06,690
Hey,Leslie.
好 Leslie

46
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:10,550
So,dumbass,I heard you made a
grad student throw up last night.
大傻冒 听说昨晚你把一研究生折腾吐了

47
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:15,780
The truth can indeed be a finger down
the throat of those unprepared to hear it.
其实是没准备好听我讲的人
自己用手指抠吐的

48
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:19,230
But why should I cater
to second-rate minds?
我干吗要去给那些二流智商的人讲课?

49
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:22,380
Because first-rate
minds call you "dumbass"?
因为智商一流的人 总喊你"傻冒儿"

50
00:03:24,510 --> 00:03:26,130
Oh,yeah?Well...
切 是吗? 嗯...

51
00:03:26,450 --> 00:03:28,730
you're a mean person.
你这个毒舌妇

52
00:03:29,660 --> 00:03:32,470
Excuse me,Dr. Cooper,I'm
Ramona Nowitzki.
打扰下 Cooper博士
我是Ramona Nowitzki

53
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:34,190
I was at your talk last night.
昨晚我听了你的讲课

54
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,870
I think you're just brilliant.
我觉得你真是天才耶

55
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:38,490
That is the prevailing opinion.
绝大多数人都这么觉得

56
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:41,380
Oh,now I'm gonna throw up.
这下我要去吐了

57
00:03:41,740 --> 00:03:44,260
Howard Wolowitz,department
of engineering,
Howard Wolowitz 工程系的

58
00:03:44,270 --> 00:03:48,860
co-designer of the International Space
Station's Liquid Waste Disposal System.
参与设计了
国际空间站液体废物处理系统

59
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,360
Dr. Cooper,I've read
everything you've published.
Cooper博士
我拜读了你发表的全部文章

60
00:03:58,380 --> 00:04:01,760
I especially liked your paper on grand
unification using string-network condensates
特别钟意那篇
从弦网浓缩角度阐述大统一理论

61
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:02,810
and was wondering how
you determined that
我很好奇 你是怎么确定

62
00:04:02,820 --> 00:04:07,340
three-dimensional string-nets provided a
unified picture of ferrnions and gauge bosons?
3D弦网提供了费密子
和规范玻色子的统一描述?

63
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:11,740
Amazing,an intelligent labradoodle.
很不错啊! 这拉布拉多真聪明!

64
00:04:12,450 --> 00:04:14,510
Woof.
汪汪

65
00:04:16,270 --> 00:04:18,490
The fact is I'm quite close
to a breakthrough in showing
其实呢 我离研究突破就差一点点

66
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:21,130
how neutrinos emerge from
a string-net condensate.
就快搞清楚
微中子如何在弦网冷凝物中脱出了

67
00:04:21,140 --> 00:04:24,780
Oh,my God,that would change the way
we view the entire physical universe.
天啦 那将会颠覆
全球对整个物理界的认识

68
00:04:24,790 --> 00:04:26,990
It's what I do.
我就是干这个的

69
00:04:27,410 --> 00:04:33,370
You know,the Pishkin-Wolowitz Liquid Waste
Disposal System is turning a few heads as well.
Pishkin-Wolowitz(两名设计者)
废液处理系统也带来一些冲击

70
00:04:36,980 --> 00:04:39,520
Again,ew.
又来了 恶心

71
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:44,630
You know,I'd love to hear more about
how you intend to add neutrinos.
我很想听你讲讲
怎样加入微中子

72
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,780
Could we get a cup of coffee sometime?
啥时候去喝杯咖啡吧?

73
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,020
I don't drink coffee.
我从不喝咖啡

74
00:04:48,030 --> 00:04:50,770
I do.I love me a cup of joe.
我喝 我爱喝咖啡了

75
00:04:51,130 --> 00:04:52,390
Well,it doesn't have to be coffee.
不一定非要喝咖啡

76
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,120
How about dinner?
一起晚餐如何?

77
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:54,410
I do eat dinner.
晚饭我还是要吃的

78
00:04:54,420 --> 00:04:56,520
Great. I know a terrific
little Italian place.
那就好 我知道有家意大利餐厅 超棒

79
00:04:56,530 --> 00:04:57,840
I never eat in strange restaurants.
我从不去陌生的餐厅吃饭

80
00:04:57,850 --> 00:05:00,980
One runs the risk of
non-standard cutlery.
指不定就用那些不标准的餐具了

81
00:05:01,890 --> 00:05:02,630
Excuse me?
啊 什么

82
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:06,340
Sheldon lives in fear
of the three-tined fork.
Sheldon对三个分叉的叉子有恐惧心理

83
00:05:06,860 --> 00:05:08,450
Three tines is not a fork.
三个分叉的根本不能叫叉子

84
00:05:08,470 --> 00:05:10,090
Three tines is a trident.
那叫三叉戟

85
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:11,200
Forks are for eating,
叉是用来吃东西的

86
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:14,230
tridents are for ruling the seven seas.
而三叉戟是用来统治七海的
(海神手中的三叉戟)

87
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:17,660
What if I brought food to your place?
要不我把吃的带去你那儿?

88
00:05:17,670 --> 00:05:19,210
That would be acceptable.
这倒行

89
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:20,870
On Mondays,I eat Thai food.
周一我吃泰国餐

90
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:24,620
Mee krob and chicken sate with
extra peanut sauce from Siam Palace.
脆炸米粉 鸡肉沙爹 加上暹罗宫的花生酱

91
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:28,460
You got it. I already have your address.
没问题 我有你家的地址

92
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,670
What a nice girl.
多好的姑娘啊

93
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:36,940
Sheldon,do you have any
idea what just happened?
Sheldon 你到底有没有搞懂刚才怎么回事

94
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:40,210
Yes. Apparently I'm
getting a free dinner.
当然 显然是有人要请我吃饭

95
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:48,340
Oh,yeah,no,this thing's
majorly out of order.
不好意思 这东西基本上不能用啦

96
00:05:48,350 --> 00:05:49,500
See? Sorry.
看吧 真不好意思

97
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:51,810
That's okay. Guess
I'm taking the stairs.
没关系 那我走楼梯咯

98
00:05:51,820 --> 00:05:52,730
Where you going?
你去哪家呢?

99
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,120
Oh,are you here to see Leonard?
是来找Leonard的吧

100
00:05:55,130 --> 00:05:57,120
No,Dr. Cooper.
不是 我找Cooper博士

101
00:05:57,130 --> 00:06:00,230
Dr. Sheldon Cooper?
你说的是Sheldon Cooper博士?

102
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:02,450
We're having dinner.
我们要共进晚餐

103
00:06:02,460 --> 00:06:05,240
Sheldon Cooper?
你确信是Sheldon Cooper?

104
00:06:06,030 --> 00:06:10,430
Tall,thin, looks a little
like a giant praying mantis?
那个瘦瘦高高 长得像
巨人版螳螂煞星

105
00:06:12,370 --> 00:06:14,990
He is cute,isn't he?
他好帅的哟 是吧

106
00:06:16,830 --> 00:06:19,540
Sheldon Cooper?
真的是Sheldon Cooper?

107
00:06:22,550 --> 00:06:23,330
Hi,Leonard.
你好Lenonand

108
00:06:23,340 --> 00:06:24,450
Hey,Ramona. Come on in.
你好Ramona 快进来

109
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:26,000
Thanks. Where should I put this?
谢谢 这些东西放哪儿呢

110
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:28,110
Uh,the kitchen's fine.
放厨房就好了

111
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,100
Hey,what are you doing?
你来有事吗?

112
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:31,070
I need to see this.
这好戏我不能错过哇

113
00:06:33,050 --> 00:06:35,490
The viewing area's right over there.
观众席在那边

114
00:06:37,610 --> 00:06:41,550
Sheldon,your girl... date...
person... Ramona's here.
Sheldon 你女朋... 约会对...Ramona来了

115
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:43,530
Oh,hello.
你好啊

116
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,750
Oh,sorry I'm late.
不好意思我迟到了

117
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:47,420
I just got so caught up reading
the draft of your latest paper.
看到你刚发表的论文草本 看得太入迷了

118
00:06:47,430 --> 00:06:50,800
Did you enjoy the humorous footnote
where I illustrate mirror-symmetry
我对镜象对称性作了一个脚注说明

119
00:06:50,810 --> 00:06:53,170
by likening it to the Flash
playing tennis with himself?
把它比喻成闪电和自己打网球
你体会到其中的幽默了吗?

120
00:06:53,180 --> 00:06:55,490
So funny.
太好笑了

121
00:06:55,900 --> 00:06:58,320
But the idea that you might
be able to incorporate gravity,
不得不提的是 你关于重力组合
可能性的猜想

122
00:06:58,350 --> 00:07:02,360
I have to tell you,I found
it physically exhilarating.
真的是让我实打实地兴奋

123
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:07,520
My hypotheses tend to have that effect.
我的假设通常都有这种效果

124
00:07:08,570 --> 00:07:10,940
I'm sorry I didn't bring
enough for your friends.
不好意思 我没给你朋友带吃的

125
00:07:10,950 --> 00:07:13,880
I assumed we were going to be alone.
我以为就我们两人

126
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:18,690
Oh,yeah. No,we were just going.
喔 没错 我们正要--

127
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:21,010
To watch,right?
准备看戏 不是吗

128
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:23,940
No,come on,now, we're going out.
快 我们马上就出门了

129
00:07:23,950 --> 00:07:26,840
Oh,come on, we'll be quiet.
别这样嘛 我们不说话成吗

130
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:29,690
Let's go,let's go.
我们还是走吧 走吧

131
00:07:29,980 --> 00:07:33,620
Okay,you two. Have a nice...
好了 祝你们俩的...随便啦

132
00:07:33,630 --> 00:07:36,520
whatever this is.
开心就是了

133
00:07:39,220 --> 00:07:41,670
Okay,you guys,look, I know
this is none of my business,
你们听好 我清楚这事压根跟我没关系

134
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:46,160
but I just... I have to
ask-- what's Sheldon's deal?
但是我还是要 忍不住想问
Sheldon的"型"到底是啥?

135
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:50,540
What do you mean "deal"?
什么"型"啊?

136
00:07:50,550 --> 00:07:52,580
You know,like what's his deal?
就是说 他好哪种型的

137
00:07:52,590 --> 00:07:56,120
Is it girls...?
Guys...? Sock puppets...?
女人 男人 布袋木偶?

138
00:07:56,590 --> 00:08:00,940
Honestly,we've been operating under
the assumption that he has no deal.
说实话 在我们的逻辑中
他根本没有"型"

139
00:08:01,260 --> 00:08:03,000
Come on,everybody has a deal.
别这样说 每个人都有喜欢的型啊

140
00:08:03,010 --> 00:08:04,010
Not Sheldon.
除了Sheldon

141
00:08:04,020 --> 00:08:08,690
Over the years,we've formulated many
theories about how he might reproduce.
多年来 我们一直潜心
试图探究他将如何繁衍后代

142
00:08:09,540 --> 00:08:12,930
I'm an advocate of mitosis.
我主张的是有丝分裂

143
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:14,720
I'm sorry?
什么?

144
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:18,450
I believe one day Sheldon will
eat an enormous amount of Thai food
我相信 总有一天 当Sheldon吃到
一定量的泰国菜

145
00:08:18,460 --> 00:08:21,560
and split into two Sheldons.
他就会分裂成两个Sheldon

146
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:26,520
On the other hand, I think Sheldon
might be the larval form of his species,
另一方面 我在想Sheldon可能
是他这个物种的幼虫状态

147
00:08:26,530 --> 00:08:31,560
and someday he'll spin a cocoon and emerge two
months later with moth wings and an exoskeleton.
有一天他会做茧
不出俩月 就破茧成蝶

148
00:08:32,590 --> 00:08:35,940
Okay,well,thanks for the nightmares.
谢谢你俩给我讲恐怖故事

149
00:08:36,850 --> 00:08:39,650
Hey,do you want to hang out with us?
要不我们一起出去逛逛

150
00:08:39,670 --> 00:08:42,330
What are you guys gonna do?
你们有什么节目

151
00:08:43,610 --> 00:08:46,630
My mom's making a brisket tonight.
我妈妈今晚作了胸肉

152
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:49,910
The one with the little onions?
那种放了小洋葱的?

153
00:08:53,090 --> 00:08:57,390
Yeah,I'm busy,so... Good night.
不好意思 我很忙 晚安吧

154
00:08:58,650 --> 00:09:01,460
Her loss. Let's go.
不去是她的损失 我们走吧

155
00:09:01,470 --> 00:09:05,340
Brisket party! B-
to-the-R-to-the-I-S-K...
胸肉聚会耶 胸 是胸肉的胸

156
00:09:06,020 --> 00:09:09,690
To-the-E-to-the-T...Ooh...
肉 是胸肉的肉 哦也

157
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:12,050
Don't.
得了吧

158
